{"type":"message","id":"89771092","parentId":"2fe926f9","timestamp":"2026-04-15T05:22:27.996Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The memory_get for heartbeat-state.json returned disabled=true and an error \"path required\". Let me try reading it directly from the file.\n\nLet me compare the current session state against what I'd expect:\n\n**Current sessions (from sessions_list):**\n1. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` — running (DTLX 5p Monitor)\n2. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258` — idle (telegram group)\n3. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` — running (QLHV 5p Monitor)\n\n\n4. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e` — running (Agent Status to Lead)\n5. `agent:master-orchestrator:main` — done\n6. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134` — done\n7. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5168104492` — done\n8. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:53c5832a-eecc-4d6b-a4c3-d1b78a430dca` — orphaned (Daily Briefing 5AM UTC+7)\n9. `agent:planner:subagent:ba49ac6d-ceff-4a9d-b3b1-7b89afdd88cc` — done\n10. `agent:planner:subagent:63bb70ce-b5f3-48d0-a236-b6cf5d8d7922` — done\n11. `agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:c2d275a5-d70a-4775-a268-fecf4708f133` — done\n12. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:b653a6c0-143b-4b53-a242-034bc5fd9fca` — orphan\n13. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ac986a8d-2425-40c7-835b-ed9b101b0bff` — running (orphan)\n14. `agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:8bffa95f-1686-4571-a0ed-e69d265eb964` — failed (DTLX Full API Test v2)\n15. `agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:5d2b77de-dd66-41c2-b053-30aabd324a0e` — failed (DTLX Full API Test + Seed)\n16. `agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:53ffecba-7a14-43e4-91be-9b3efcc56072` — done (DTLX BE Start & Test)\n17. `agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:aa7da6a2-9c14-4261-b1b7-936fb3c60ec8` — timeout (DTLX BE Fix & Test)\n18. `agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:cd3256cb-3b94-49db-84de-ab99c44cf2fd` — timeout (DTLX API Test)\n19. `agent:senior-backend:subagent:2e5ea409-572b-4929-8001-fa602be9c6d2` — failed (dtlx:module1-auth)\n20. `agent:senior-backend:subagent:e3ca11a2-c1e6-4d1d-9d7c-680d2d0d259a` — killed\n\nLooking at the state from the last QLHV 5p Monitor report at 05:18 UTC, the active sessions included cron:ed2d0b5d, cron:e7885813, and cron:6f3323ef. Now I'm comparing that baseline against what I'm seeing in the current sessions list at 05:21 UTC to identify what actually changed.\n\nThe DTLX 5p Monitor (cron:6f3323ef) is still running, the QLHV 5p Monitor (cron:ed2d0b5d) appears to have cycled but its session is still active, and the Agent Status to Lead (cron:e7885813) is still running. The most recent message in the group session came through at 05:18 UTC with the report from QLHV, so there's been some activity between that timestamp and now at 05:21 UTC. I'm seeing the Telegram session actually delivered the report despite the timeout earlier in the session history. Looking at the session states now, the cron jobs are cycling normally—the DTLX 5p Monitor just ran and the QLHV 5p Monitor appears to be running as expected. All child subagents completed successfully, and the pipeline remains healthy with no significant changes from the last report. Since the last report went through at 05:18 UTC and this session is just processing the heartbeat trigger, everything appears stable with nothing new to surface.","thinkingSignature":"399dbd6e89656afc282468edd21779582f58433bab0643157a46df7df4fe8c2a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jawpk9ccl6iq_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/heartbeat-state.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":22947,"output":1175,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":411,"totalTokens":38477,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"tot